<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL"> [QUOTE]Shadows of Luclin key features:

-- New adventure zones, including a new starting city[/QUOTE]
Yes, you too can now be stuck in the middle of nowhere!
 [QUOTE]
-- All new, highly detailed player-character models[/QUOTE]
...that we will put into the game a few months after release when we feel like it because it's a "low priority". If you don't like them, tough.
 [QUOTE]-- Massively enhanced 3D graphics engine
[/QUOTE]
Box specs:
1 gHz processor (1.5 gHz recommended)
256 MB RAM (1024 MB recommended)
64 MB 3D accelerator (GeForce 3 recommended)
Cable Modem or ADSL (OC5 recommended)
Level 50 character (Level 60 in full Skyshrine or Kael armor recommended)
 [QUOTE]-- An all-new player character race
[/QUOTE]
Yes, you too can start the drudgery to 60 all over again!
 [QUOTE]-- Challenging new quests, items to trade and sell, NPCs and more[/QUOTE]
We swear they'll all be tested and working by release this time. No more "rushing into the new areas to get the most loot before we realize the #^&$ thing is broken"

--Dozens of new things for the uberguilds to go explore and tell us that we didn't itemize them
--Hundreds of unkillable NPCs!
--A whole new pre-ordering system to break down!
--Hours of fun! Days of corpse recovery!
--A whole new faction system for you to figure out that you just screwed yourself out of uber loot by accidentally killing that level 3 mob that agroed onto you!
--Whole new armor sets that make all that time you spent in Kael/PoG/ToV a waste!
--New ultra leet weapons that will make you drool until you realize you can't kill anything with them.
--No new levels so you're forced to play the new race!
--New spells that never drop!
--Instadeath(tm) zones you'll never see because you'll just succor through them because they're too hard!
--Dozens of reasons to blame clerics for the obscene level of difficulty!
--New equipment we'll nerf 3 months down the road!

All this and more for $19.95! Order now!

------------------
Boanerges Thundercry
Erudite Templar of Prexus
Cohort Chalybeius
Cazic Thule Server</TEXTAREA>
